# tc_kitchenconfigurator module

## Architecture

- **PHP:** `tc_kitchenconfigurator.php` — `GROUPS_DEF` constant, `processBoSave()`, `normalizeRows()`, `handleBoImageUpload()`.
- **AJAX controller:** `controllers/front/ajax.php` — JSON endpoint for FO form; calls `$this->module->handleFrontFormSubmit()`.
- **BO template:** `views/templates/admin/configure.tpl` — Smarty repeater with inline `<script>` (no external JS file).
- **FO template:** `views/templates/hook/kitchenconfigurator.tpl` — front-office form with `data-tc-kcfg-ajax-url` attribute.
- **FO JS:** `_dev/js/custom/Sections/TcKitchenConfigurator.js` — card interactions + AJAX submit.
- **Config storage:** `Configuration::updateValue()` with JSON-encoded groups.
- **Emails:** `inquiry.html/.txt` (to shop), `inquiry_confirmation.html/.txt` (to customer).

## Anti-bot / CSRF

- Cookie token (`COOKIE_TOKEN`, `COOKIE_TOKEN_TTL`) — 10 min TTL, rotated after every submit.
- Honeypot field `tc_kcfg_url` (hidden, must stay empty).
- Token hidden input `tc_kcfg_token` matched against cookie value.
- PSGDPR consent checked when module is enabled.

## BO repeater — JS in Smarty templates

The add/remove/reindex logic is inline JS in `configure.tpl`.

When writing `new RegExp()` inside a Smarty `.tpl` file, do **not** double-escape backslashes for Smarty — Smarty does not process `\`:

```javascript
// ❌ BAD — over-escaped, regex never matches [0], [1] etc.
name.replace(new RegExp('kcfg_' + g + '\\\\[\\\\d+\\\\]'), ...)

// ✅ GOOD — standard JS escaping only
name.replace(new RegExp('kcfg_' + g + '\\[\\d+\\]'), ...)
```

## PHP — normalizeRows()

- Rows with empty `title` are silently dropped.
- `id` is auto-generated as `{groupKey}_{idx+1}` if not provided.
- Images use `$_FILES['kcfg_image_{groupKey}'][index]`.
